snippet: Thousands of military enthusiasts in trucks, jeeps and other Army vehicles converged on Normandy, France, to mark the 70th anniversary of D-Day.
abstract: Thousands of military enthusiasts in trucks, jeeps and other Army vehicles converge in Normandy, France, to mark the 70th anniversary of the D-Day invasion; historic event involves some 50,000 tanks, halftracks, armored cars, bulldozers, motorcycles and other assorted machines that have fascinated collectors ever since.
lead_paragraph: Thousands of military enthusiasts in trucks, jeeps and other Army vehicles converged on Normandy, France, to mark the 70th anniversary of D-Day.
